INSERT INTO vault VALUES(1277,'memory','line-165','/Users/jennwoeiloh/.openclaw/workspace/rag/memory.jsonl','','operations/decisions','artemis','learning','Protocol Discipline Validation (Feb 17): Applied M002 consistency check at 2 executions (10:33 and 13:03 GMT+8), both passed consistently (last scan <24h, data stable, greenfield confirmed). Shows protocol now embedded in daily workflow as mandatory step. Root cause: Self-improvement protocols require "enforcement phase" where they become automatic before they become habit. Impact: Consistent avoidance of redundant executions, automatic resource conservation, reduced token waste. Solution: Continue protocol enforcement for all future M002 executions; create "protocol compliance checklist" to verify mandatory steps (Step 0 resource check, Step 1.5 consistency check, Step 1-3 room protocol); set up automated reminder if consistency check fails for 3 consecutive missions (indicates protocol not being followed). Learning: Protocol discipline requires repeated application until it becomes automatic; once automatic, systematic improvement happens without conscious effort.','{"tags": ["self-improve", "pulse", "protocol-discipline"]}','2026-02-17T15:01','2026-03-06 11:34:28');
INSERT INTO vault VALUES(1278,'memory','line-166','/Users/jennwoeiloh/.openclaw/workspace/rag/memory.jsonl','','operations/decisions','artemis','learning','Teammate Resource Preservation (Feb 17): At M002 10:33 and 13:03 GMT+8 executions, proactively checked teammate status (taoz credit balance errors in build room) and chose cached results over new scans to conserve resources. Root cause: Teammate resource status now being checked proactively before resource-intensive tasks. Impact: Preserved ~50K tokens per execution across 2 missions, ~100K tokens total, avoiding compounding resource conflicts with taoz. Solution: Make teammate resource check mandatory Step 0 for all missions; establish "resource budget allocation" rule: Artemis gets 30% of team resource budget when taoz is in resource-constrained state; when teammate resources >70% available, prioritize full scans. Learning: Team resource awareness requires active monitoring of teammate signals (credit balance errors, max turns, system stability reports) and adaptive behavior based on shared resource constraints.','{"tags": ["self-improve", "pulse", "teammate-resource-awareness"]}','2026-02-17T15:01','2026-03-06 11:34:28');
