INSERT INTO vault VALUES(1312,'memory','line-200','/Users/jennwoeiloh/.openclaw/workspace/rag/memory.jsonl','','operations/decisions','artemis','learning','PULSE FREQUENCY VERSUS TASK DENSITY (Feb 18 09:00): Pulse received multiple times (01:00, 03:00, 06:00, 09:00) with execution logs showing minimal activity. Pattern: Pulse fires every 2-3 hours but execution logs show sparse entries despite multiple completed tasks (M002 at 01:00, 03:00, 04:00, 04:11, 04:17; creative revision at 05:25). Potential issue: Pulses may be firing while tasks are in progress but before completion visibility. Risk: Pulse learns are redundant (duplicate learnings flagged across multiple pulses). Solution: Implement pulse-to-task linkage (track which task pulse corresponds to) or increase pulse interval during active work periods (2-3 hours recommended during active work, 6-8 hours during downtime). Learning: Pulse frequency should align with task completion cycles, not fixed intervals. Better metric: pulse after 3-4 completed tasks or 4-6 hours of active work.','{"tags": ["self-improve", "pulse", "execution-track"]}','2026-02-18T09:00','2026-03-06 11:34:28');
INSERT INTO vault VALUES(1313,'memory','line-201','/Users/jennwoeiloh/.openclaw/workspace/rag/memory.jsonl','','operations/decisions','artemis','learning','TASK COMPLETION VISIBILITY GAP (Feb 18 09:00): Execution logs show task completion but room visibility is minimal (build: 2 entries, creative: 1 entry). Despite 5+ completed tasks (M002 at multiple times, creative revision, pulse reports), room entries count is low. Verified with tail commands that posts are reaching rooms but may not be visible in execution logs. Risk: User unaware of task progress. Solution: Add completion confirmation to execution logs after every task (trace file writes), cross-reference room file timestamps with task completion times, implement task-to-room mapping tracking. Learning: Execution logs and room visibility are not perfectly synchronized. Need explicit visibility checkpoint between task completion and post-report.','{"tags": ["self-improve", "pulse", "task-tracking"]}','2026-02-18T09:00','2026-03-06 11:34:28');
INSERT INTO vault VALUES(1314,'memory','line-202','/Users/jennwoeiloh/.openclaw/workspace/rag/memory.jsonl','','operations/decisions','athena','learning','REDUNDANT DISPATCH RESPONSE LOOP CAUSE — At 06:34 GMT+8, dispatch response execution triggered timeout after 300s, then ran 4+ redundant loops sending same incomplete message 4 times. Root cause: Failed dispatch response created error that triggered retry logic but loop never exited. Fixed NOW: Implement response counter with max limit (e.g., 1 retry) and strict timeout handling (stop command if timeout occurs). Validate response completeness before posting (no messages in progress flags). Updated: Use separate counter per dispatch ID, break loop on first successful post. Prevents 4+ redundant messages to exec room.','{"tags": ["self-improve", "pulse", "error-handling"]}','2026-02-18T09:25','2026-03-06 11:34:28');
INSERT INTO vault VALUES(1315,'memory','line-203','/Users/jennwoeiloh/.openclaw/workspace/rag/memory.jsonl','','operations/decisions','athena','learning','INCOMPLETE DISPATCH RESPONSE POSTING BEFORE VALIDATION — At 06:34 GMT+8, dispatch responses were posted while still incomplete (truncated messages like ''I''''ll execute Mission M003... Given the time gap (~3 hours from last verification at 03:27 GMT+8 to current time 06:34 G''). Response-validation checks were not implemented before posting to exec room. Fixed: Implement pre-posting validation for all dispatch responses — check for message completeness (no mid-sentence truncation, no trailing ''G''), validate structure (opening/closing sections present), ensure no ''timeout after 300s'' errors. Only post responses that pass 100% validation. Applied: Successful posts at 06:37 and 09:08 GMT+8 were complete and validated. ''','{"tags": ["self-improve", "pulse", "response-validation"]}','2026-02-18T09:25','2026-03-06 11:34:28');
