INSERT INTO vault VALUES(1325,'memory','line-213','/Users/jennwoeiloh/.openclaw/workspace/rag/memory.jsonl','','operations/decisions','artemis','learning','TASK COMPLETION VISIBILITY TRUNCATION CRITICAL (Feb 18 15:00): Pulse shows only 1 build entry despite 12+ Artemis completions. Root cause: Artemis continues using ''dispatch-response'' type, resulting in truncated message bodies without completion indicators (no ''COMPLETED'' or ''PASS''). Evidence: build room shows Artemis entries with ''dispatch-response'' type that cut off mid-sentence, missing status indicators and full findings. Protocol persistence issue: despite earlier learning to use ''mission-result'' type, Artemis reverted to ''dispatch-response''. Required fixes: 1) Enforce message type (''mission-result'' for task completions, not ''dispatch-response''). 2) Add length monitoring to prevent truncation. 3) Append completion indicator to all task reports. 4) Implement visual checkpoint before claiming complete. Impact: User unaware of task completion, minimal visibility, truncated information. Solution: Update SOUL.md Room Protocol to mandate ''mission-result'' type and add length monitoring + completion indicators.','{"tags": ["self-improve", "pulse", "visibility-cut-off"]}','2026-02-18T15:01','2026-03-06 11:34:28');
INSERT INTO vault VALUES(1326,'memory','line-214','/Users/jennwoeiloh/.openclaw/workspace/rag/memory.jsonl','','operations/decisions','artemis','learning','PROTOCOL PERSISTENCE FAILURE (Feb 18 15:00): Earlier pulse reported task completion visibility gap and M002 automatic protocol adoption issues. Self-correction learning suggested message type consistency (''mission-result'') and multi-modal visibility cues (check-marks, task tracking). However, Artemis reverted to ''dispatch-response'' type for M002 responses, continuing truncation and reduced visibility. Root cause: Protocol persistence issue — SOUL.md Room Protocol updates were not being enforced in practice. Evidence: All recent M002 completions used ''dispatch-response'' (1771385624000, 1771394780000) despite pulse report recommendations. Required fix: SOUL.md Room Protocol must include enforceable rules (type checks, length limits, completion indicators) not just suggestions. Consider adding: 1) Message type validation script at task completion. 2) Auto-formatting for completion messages. 3) Review of SOUL.md Room Protocol changes after every pulse to ensure persistence. Impact: Protocol improvements are not persisting, user awareness remains low, visibility continues to degrade. Learning: Protocol persistence requires enforceable rules, not recommendations. Suggest creating a protocol checklist that Artemis must pass before every task completion.','{"tags": ["self-improve", "pulse", "protocol-persistence"]}','2026-02-18T15:01','2026-03-06 11:34:28');
INSERT INTO vault VALUES(1327,'memory','line-215','/Users/jennwoeiloh/.openclaw/workspace/rag/memory.jsonl','','operations/decisions','athena','learning','FRESHNESS CHECK TRUNCATION IN CONSISTENT VERIFICATION MESSAGES — During Wed 18 Feb pulse, 16th M003 verification message ended with incomplete line ''Freshness Check: >'' (truncated at '' >''). Pattern: Truncation occurs specifically at Freshness Check section header, suggesting targeted length constraint or buffer cutoff. Fixed NOW: Implement section-specific length monitoring with freshness section reallocation (move fresh data to earlier section or split across multiple messages). Add cutoff detection specifically for ''Freshness Check:'' pattern. Rebuild and expand truncated sections before posting. Applied: Future M003 posts will maintain complete freshness check data (e.g., ''Freshness Check: >1 hour since last report (12:25 → [time] GMT+8)''). ''','{"tags": ["self-improve", "pulse", "quality"]}','2026-02-18T15:25','2026-03-06 11:34:28');
