INSERT INTO vault VALUES(1331,'memory','line-219','/Users/jennwoeiloh/.openclaw/workspace/rag/memory.jsonl','','operations/decisions','artemis','learning','PROTOCOL v3 TITLE ADOPTION WITHOUT TYPE ENFORCEMENT (Feb 18 18:00): Artemis implemented Protocol v3 title changes (''FRESH SCAN (Protocol v3 with Enforceable Rules)'') but underlying message type remains ''dispatch-response'' (not ''mission-result''). Evidence: Build room entry 1771403891000 shows new title format but still uses ''dispatch-response'' type, not the mandated ''mission-result'' type. Root cause: SOUL.md Room Protocol recommended enforceable rules (message type validation, length monitoring) but Artemis reverted to mental checklist without actual enforcement script. Required fix: Create explicit validation script for every post that enforces: 1) Message type = ''mission-result'' (not ''dispatch-response''). 2) Length < 5000 chars. 3) Completion indicator present. 4) Agent name in message. Execute validation script before every post. Impact: Title adoption without actual enforcement, protocol improvements not persisting, user awareness remains low. Solution: Create SOUL.md Room Protocol enforcement script that runs before every post, validate and fail if rules not met.','{"tags": ["self-improve", "pulse", "protocol-enforcement"]}','2026-02-18T18:01','2026-03-06 11:34:28');
INSERT INTO vault VALUES(1332,'memory','line-220','/Users/jennwoeiloh/.openclaw/workspace/rag/memory.jsonl','','operations/decisions','artemis','learning','BUILD ROOM VISIBILITY CONSISTENCY ISSUE (Feb 18 18:00): Pulse shows only 1 build room entry (M002 at 16:25) despite 13+ Artemis completions throughout day (01:00, 03:00, 04:00, 04:11, 04:17, 06:00, 06:33, 09:05, 09:33, 11:33, 14:05, 15:00 pulse, 16:33, 16:35, now 18:00 pulse). Evidence: Build room entries show Artemis posts at 1771385624000 (11:33), 1771394780000 (14:05), 1771403891000 (16:35), but pulse only counts ''1 entry''. Possible issue: Tail command may be truncated, message type filtering, or room file size limits. Root cause: Inconsistent visibility verification between pulse reports and actual room content. Required fix: Implement mandatory visibility checkpoint after every post with explicit verification: 1) Check build room file has Artemis entry with correct timestamp. 2) Verify message type = ''mission-result''. 3) Verify completion indicator present. 4) Count entries and log if != expected count. Execute checkpoint before pulse to ensure visibility. Impact: User unaware of task completion count, unclear system state, visibility degradation persists. Solution: Add ''visibility_checkpoint'' function in SOUL.md Room Protocol that runs before every post and logs result to execution room. Then pulse uses verified count from checkpoint.','{"tags": ["self-improve", "pulse", "post-checkpoint"]}','2026-02-18T18:01','2026-03-06 11:34:28');
